10
The Community sheet is based on data reported by members in the Fisherman's Horizon discord.
11
Ruby Route, Fish by Route, Shellfish, Squid and Shrimp sheets are created by/based on data gathered by Tyo'to Tayuun from video recordings of voyages so far.
12
Bite times are accurate but not comprehensive as the dataset for all baits and IC-Cast tests is still far too small. See Indigo below on how this is done.
13
Ruby introduces new bite archetypes to spectral currents. More fish are able to be blind TH/DHed than it may appear by early impressions/looking at data.
14
Thank you to B'runi Masna and Mia Coda for providing me additional VODs to review in order to get more accurate data faster.
15
Blue bait is the bait with the highest bite rate based on the current dataset, or best to use for Spectral fish/Leopard Shrimp (see cell notes). Green can also catch the fish.
16
17
INDIGO ROUTE:
18
All data was manually collected and has image/video proof that was recorded on stream by Tyo'to Tayuun.
19
Bite time data is based on in-game Cast macro timings, is bait-specific and was gathered using the following method:
20
1) Find the approximate window of time in which the fish bites and make a macro that contains all relevant intervals specific to that fish.
21
2) Catch the fish, use Identical Cast, Cast multiple times until the stop/spectral current was over.
22
Record video of ~200 bites for each fish with each bait. Rewatch footage of the bites at 0.25x speed to ensure accuracy.
23
3) If the fish cannot have Identical Cast used on it, ~100 bites were recorded and rewatched in the above method.
24
The exception is the 5-star/blue fish due to their rarity, but crowdsourced data supports their minimum bite time.
25
If multiple baits are usable, the one highlighted in blue is the one a fish bites on most often*. Ones in green can also catch the fish but the fish is less likely to bite on them.
26
If multiple baits are usable, a different bait can be better to use to target a specific fish either due to its bite times, bite rates on other fish, or a combination of both.
27
This is not accounted for in this sheet except for Spectral Megalodon.
28
Weather impacts optimal bait usage for specific fish when outside of spectral currents due to weather other than Fair Skies removing fish.
29
This is also not accounted for except for Spectral Megalodon.
